The President of the United States, at the time, offered his condolences to the Argentine people and President Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner on the death of Nestor Kirchner, former President of Argentina and Secretary General of the Union of South American Nations (UNASUR). Nestor Kirchner was an influential figure in Argentine politics and was beginning a new chapter with UNASUR. The President expressed his thoughts and prayers for President Fernandez de Kirchner and their children.